CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 28, 1956, pg. 28, reads: "'Operation Big Feed' - Taking an active part in State Game Conservation program is the Bucktail Hunting and Fishing Club. Its members recently purchased 3,400 pounds of corn which it will distribute to deer in the mountains. Ready for their third annual feeding trip are, left to right, 'Al' Wilkins (in truck), Clifton Poinsette, A. J. Scott, L. P. Newson, James Smith and Henry D. Williams. The club will hold its third annual game dinner Saturday night at the Court of Calanthe Hall, Centre Avenue. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Bucktail Hunting and Fishing Club members, from left: driver "Al" Wilkins, Clifton Poinsette, A. J. Scott, L. P. Newson, James Smith, and Henry D. Williams gathered around truck parked in front of Handelman's Sandwich Shop and their clubhouse shop front at 2105 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
